cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.HC 

This paper analyzes the evolution of ego-networks in social media, which involves the study of social interactions and recommendations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the impact of link recommender systems, which falls under the scope of cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). Additionally, the paper uses matching and link prediction experiments, which are related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
